reviews.review_text: Beautiful Matrix The Loser and Looks Like Rain are explosive. Garcia's solos have that machine gun quality- real full tone with an edgy bite. Phil bombs away on China-Rider.
Crowd noise I love the intro when the guy says "what the f*** are you doing- I'm taping this!" as he's picking up the mike! Little did he know...
Upgrade Available! A HUGE upgrade of this matrix now circulates. Almost all songs were re-synced. Hope you enjoy it.

Sound quality & performance are superb Although I am a late 80's head, my brother turned me on to the early 80's matrix recordings put together by Hunter Seamons. This is one of the crispest recordings to be found on the archive, and it highlights the creativity that Brent brought to the band. 

The Cassidy jam is outrageous and the China/Rider, as was stated previously, was an absolute machine gun. (For those who want more machine gun, check out Rocco Prestia on the Tower of Power's "Out of Oakland." Bass, I know. But machine gun nonetheless.) 

Playin' is one of the best I've heard and easily competes with some of the '88 and '89 masterpieces, particularly Oxford '88.

Altogether an unbelievable show. I envy anyone who attended.
Great show & very good recording, but this version has been superseded by recent Seamons upgrades, both 16 & 24 bit, that are tremendous. See other copies.

my 4th Cali show Born in 62 growing up in so. cal. 74 found me and my fam living other places. Became a DH in MD. in 80. My fam. moved back to Cal. in the spring of 82 and this was my 4th Cali show after Ventura.
Wow what a place and show. This one was the real deal.

MY FAVORITE Was at this show. Blown away at the song list. One of my all  time best China Cat. Then Bobby getting one side of the crowd to sing I CAN'T GET NO and the other side SATISFACTION!!! 
Truly an epic SHOW

Jerry Jerry's guitar break in Sugar Mag is awesome....

The Wheel is quite nice, as well....
